result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob Aaron Callan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jacob Aaron Callan in court.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  P&P Agent, Olivia McKinney appears by phone.  Court informs defendant in 2016 he was placed on probation and ordered to pay restitution & court costs, restitution determined in the amount of $7250.  Information filed by DOC says $2787 remains unpaid.  Mr. Callan does not disagree.  Restitution was joint & several with co-defendants.  State informs co-defendant Anthony Goviera has paid $3000 - $4000 and victim didn't want anymore paid by Mr. Goviera.  State needs accurate payments made by Mr. Callan and he not get credit made by co-defendants..  DOC Agent informs Mr. Callan has paid $130.  $5000 was paid of which Mr. Callan paid $130.  Mr. Callan believes he paid approx. $300.  He's in school full time and was layed up for awhile.  Agent informs Mr. Callan went to Teen Challenged and did a really really good job.  His mother is trying to pay the debt.  Court extends probation for 1 year, if pay balance of restitution owed of $2786.88 will discharge probation.  $1253.06 for court ordered obligations will also have to be paid before court will discharge you and paid through P&P and get receipts and present to the court.  Court orders Mr. Callan pay a minimum of $200/mo. com. 2/4 and 1st Monday every month thereafter.  DOC to notify the court any month Mr. Callan does not pay $200.

Defendant Jacob Aaron Callan in court with attorney Erika Amundson.  Defendant Jacob Aaron Callan in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel confirms with the court receipt of the 4/17/17 letter from DOC.  Court notes an earlier motion on failure to complete community service not yet resolved.  State informs of discussions prior to hearing this morning for defendant to enter into another program in Milwaukee.  State notes DOC recommendation 60 to 90 days conditional jail and enter into a faith based treatment program which the department is in favor of.
